node.text:
Some of my go-tos! Enjoy 😊 

Greek Inspired Salad Jar
* 1-2 cups kale
* 1 tbsp feta cheese
* 4oz chicken thighs 
* 10 olives 
* ¼ cup red onion 
* ½ orange bell pepper 
* ½ cup chickpeas
* 1 tbsp balsamic

BLT Remix Salad jar 
* 1 cup mixed greens
* 2 pieces nitrate free bacon
* 2 eggs 
* ½ cup cucumber 
* 1 cup tomatoes 
* 2 tbsp paleo ranch

Veggie Goddess
* 1 cup mixed greens
* ½ cup red onion 
* ½ cup black beans 
* ½ cup quinoa
* ½ cup cucumber 
* ½ cup tomatoes 
* 1 tbsp balsamic

Tex Mex Jar Combo 
* 1 tbsp cilantro 
* 2 cup lettuce   
* 4oz ground turkey or grass-fed ground beef
* ½ cup corn
* ¼ cup onion 
* ½ cup bell peppers 
* ½ cup tomatoes 
* 1 tbsp balsamic

Coconut oil pulling benefits:
Fights bad breath,
improves gum health &
maintains teeth whitness.

What to do:
Step 1: Swish 1 tbsp coconut oil in your mouth for 10-15 min (yes min!) Step 2: Spit in trash afterwards since oil will clog the drains
Step 3: Brush your teeth normally after and floss like you normally would.

Cheers to great oral health!
Xoxo
Amanda

node.text:
How to make chicken not suck! 🍗 (swipe to see ingredients in each marinade)⁠
⁠
Looking to switch up your chicken routine? I got you covered. These combos are simple and easy to whip up for the week. In the photo, I’m using my silicone, reusable, dishwasher safe stasher bag to marinade the chicken to help cut down on my use of plastic for the environment and for me!⁠
⁠
What to do: ⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⁠
1. Combine ingredients in a bowl.⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⁠
2. Place chicken and marinade a bag.⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⁠
3. Marinade in fridge for 2 hours.⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⁠
4. Bake for 25 min @ 450 degrees for a 7oz breast⁠
⁠
Below are the marinades. Each makes 1 serving, multiply for each chicken breast you have.⁠
⁠
Cilantro lime:⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⁠
1 tbsp olive oil⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⁠
1 lime⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⁠
1 tsp honey ⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⁠
1/4 cup cilantro leaves chopped⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⁠
1 clove garlic minced⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⁠
Sea salt  to taste⁠
⁠
Coconut Curry :⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⁠
1/2 cup full fat coconut milk⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⁠
1 tbsp red curry paste⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⁠
1 tbsp curry powder⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⁠
1 lime ⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⁠
Sea salt to tase⁠
⁠
Jalapeño Lime Marinade⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⁠
1 lime⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⁠
1 tbsp avocado oil⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⁠
1-2 jalapeños, cut⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⁠
Sea salt to taste⁠
⁠
Lemon ginger:⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⁠
1 tbsp olive oil⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⁠
1 lemon ⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⁠
1 tsp minced ginger⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⁠
1/8 tsp red pepper flake⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⁠
Sea salt to taste⁠
⁠
Inspired by sweetpeasandsaffron.com & eatthegains.com⠀⠀⠀⠀⁠⁠

node.text:
The power of marketing ( ⏩ swipe to see some much better choices)⁠⁠
⁠⁠
It’s crazy how much marketing can shape and mold our opinion of certain brands. Let’s be real - it’s because marketing works!⁠⁠
⁠⁠
However, it is becoming increasingly important that we become conscious consumers and really start to question if brands actually live it up to the stories and claims they put out there.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
The marketing thrown at children these days, with highly processed foods especially irritates me. So many boxes covered in cartoons and colorful imagery trying to draw kids in.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
The Hawaiian Punch for example is pretty much just water & high fructose corn syrup with food dyes - yikes! Less that 2% is made from real fruit juices yet the company happily displays all the wonderful fruit on the front of the package.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
As for gatorade, the amount of marketing tying that brand in with pro-athletes is unbelievable. Yet, a simple choice like coconut water full of natural electrolytes and natural sugars would be much better than all the filler ingredients added to this drink along with the blue food dye. I’ve also added some more options for athletes in the third graphic.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Water is also such an under appreciated macronutrient but I’m advocating we start putting water back on its pedestal! If you’re looking to add more flavor to your daily water, try incorporating fresh fruits or herbs in your batches of water.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
I hope you found this helpful! Let me know what other brands you’d like me to talk about. Xoxo,⁠⁠
Amanda⁠⁠
.⁠⁠
.⁠⁠

9 Weight Loss Swaps! (*Swipe to see more) Want to lose weight without counting calories? I got you covered! Not only will these swaps help your waist line but they’re also help your overall heath. Lower sugar and less processed food choices for the win!⁠⠀⁠
⁠⠀⁠
And while it’s perfectly great to treat ourselves, it’s what we do repeatedly that can make or break us! ⁠So think of these as easy swaps you can make on most days 😁⠀⁠
⁠⠀⁠
🍓 Fruit smoothie ➡️ homemade protein shake - Fruit smoothies are often sugar bombs in disguise. Skip the processed sugar trap and make your own protein shake with fruit at home!⁠⠀⁠
⁠⠀⁠
🍚 Burrito ➡️ burrito bowl - While you might not want to give up the beloved chipotle, a burrito bowl instead of a burrito is an easy swap.⁠⠀⁠
⁠⠀⁠
🍫 Candy bar ➡️ dark chocolate - Save the sugar and calories by going for a quality chocolate bar instead.⁠⠀⁠
⁠⠀⁠
🍿 Chips ➡️ Popcorn - Popcorn is an easy grab-n-go food and much less processed than chips!⁠⠀⁠
⁠⠀⁠
☕️ Frappuccino ➡️Iced Coffee w/ Coconut Milk - A grande mocha has 61g sugar & 400 calories while an unsweetened iced coffee with coconut milk contains 25 calories & 2g sugar.⁠⠀⁠
⁠⠀⁠
🍔 Burger with bun ➡️ burger lettuce wrap - Save yourself the extra processed carbs when you swap a bun for a lettuce warp.⁠⠀⁠
⁠⠀⁠
🍌 Banana chips ➡️ Banana - While banana chips are yummy, it’s much easier to overeat than a banana.⁠⠀⁠
⁠⠀⁠
🥯 Bagel ➡️ Rice cake - Rice cakes are light, easy & go with almost any topping. Plus, they only contain 2 ingredients: rice & salt.⁠⠀⁠
⁠⠀⁠
🥤 Naked juice ➡️ kombucha - 16 oz bottle of kombucha is only 50 cals & 12g sugar while naked juice is 270 cals & 53g sugar.⁠⠀⁠
⁠⠀⁠
P.S. if you’re looking for comprehensive nutrition book to support your health goals, I’ve you covered - link in bio!⁠
.⠀⁠⠀⁠
.⠀⁠⠀⁠

#AD | 6 Delicious Ways to Enjoy Sweet Cherries! 🍒 Which way is your fav? (Swipe to see what’s in each combo and some benefits of cherries)

Sweet Northwest Cherries are definitely one of my favorite fruits, especially this time of year! Sweet cherries have so many health benefits, like their fiber content, antioxidants, sleep benefits, and more. Plus they’re refreshing AF and can be paired with almost anything! 

Make sure to check out @nwcherrygrowers for more cherry recipes and fun ideas. Some more fun facts about cherries below: 

👉 Anthocyanins found in cherries can help lower inflammation & lower your risk of cardiovascular disease.
👉 Improved memory & cognitive function was shown in the elderly population when consuming anthocyanins.
👉 Cherries have a lower glycemic index than almost any other fruit.
👉 The polyphenols in cherries can help reduce oxidative stress & lower inflammation 

Check out my ideas below:⁠

1️⃣ Dip ⅔ of each @nwcherrygrowers cherry into melted dark chocolate ⁠and top with a sprinkle of sea salt. Then, lay them on a plate covered with parchment paper. Let sit in the fridge for at least 10 minutes⠀⁠
2️⃣ Make a decadent chocolate cherry protein smoothie. In mine, I use chocolate protein powder, unsweetened almond milk, 1 cup pitted cherries, ¼ cup coconut flakes and 1 banana. 
3️⃣ Create a yogurt parfait with 1 cup Greek yogurt, sweet cherries, honey and granola.
4️⃣ Include them in a flavor-packed fruit salad with some of your other favorite fruits like peaches, strawberries, blackberries, blueberries, etc. 
5️⃣ Eat them by themselves - so good!!⠀⠀⁠
6️⃣ Make chia pudding with 2 tbsp chia seeds, 1/2 cup vanilla almond milk, 1 tsp maple syrup, @nwcherrygrowers cherries + monk fruit.

Hope you love these!⠀⁠
Xx⠀⁠
Amanda

Want a refreshing and delicious way to stay cool this summer? I got you covered with these colorful Iced Tea recipes! 🍊🥒🍓🍋 (*swipe to see the ingredients in each iced tea)⠀⠀⠀⁠⁠
⁠
Staying hydrated is the name of the game when it comes to reaching your goals & feeling your best! Many people struggle to find alternatives to high calorie coffee drinks, juices, soda etc. That’s why I put together these delicious iced tea recipes that are loaded with flavor & low in sugar.⠀⁠⁠
⠀⁠⁠
Here’s how to prepare each:⁠
(makes about a pitcher of tea each) ⠀⠀⁠⁠
⁠
1- Raspberry Lime: Boil 2 cups of water. Once boiling, remove from heat, add ½ cup raspberries, lime juice, 1 tbsp honey and place in 2 hibiscus tea bags. Let steep for 4-5 minutes. Once cool, sift out the raspberries and pour into a pitcher. Finally, add in fresh fruit & enjoy! ⁠
⁠
2- Pineapple Ginger: Boil 2 cups of water. Once boiling, add in 1 tsp grated ginger, remove from heat, and place in 2 rooibos tea bags w/ 1 tbsp honey. Let steep for 5-6 minutes. Once cool, sift out the ginger & pour into a blender with ½ cup pineapple. Blend until smooth, sift out the pulp and pour into the pitcher of your choice. Then add in fresh pineapple! ⁠
⁠
3- Peach Blueberry : Boil 2 cups of water. Once boiling, remove from heat, add ½ cup of blueberries, 1 tbsp honey & place in 2 White tea bags. Let steep for 4-5 minutes. Once cool, sift out blueberries, pour into a pitcher & add in fresh peaches & blueberries. ⁠
⁠
4- Strawberry Mint: Boil 2 cups of water. Once boiling, remove from heat, add ½ cup of blueberries,in 2-3 sprigs mint, 1 tbsp honey and place in 2 Mint tea bags. Let steep for 10-12 minutes. Once cool, sift out mint leaves, pour into a pitcher & add in fresh strawberries & mint leaves.⁠
⁠
5- Matcha Basil:  Boil 2 cups of water. Once boiling, add in 4-5 basil leaves, 2 tbsps lemon juice, & remove from heat. In a separate bowl, combine ¼ cup of water with 1 tsp matcha powder & stir until well combined. Once the basil water has cooled, add in 1 tbsp honey and sift out the basil leaves. Next combine the basil water with the matcha & pour into the pitcher of your choice. Add in fresh lemon slices, basil leaves, & enjoy! ⠀⁠

Say Cheese 🧀😁 (▶️Swipe to see some better choices when it comes to cheese)⠀⠀⁠
.⠀⠀⁠
While I know you most likely wouldn’t eat American “cheese” on a salad, I wanted to point out how ridiculous this cheese looks. American “cheese” is also called Pasteurized Processed Cheese Food which is only required to be at least 51% real cheese. It’s typically combined with cheap filler ingredients & emulsifiers. Also note, there are “cheeses” that contain less than 51% cheese and will then be labelled “cheese product”.⠀⠀⁠
.⠀⠀⁠
There are definitely higher quality choices of cheese out there. Many of the better choices are fermented & contain beneficial probiotics that make them easier-to-digest than their overly processed counterparts. Now, remember a large portion of the population is lactose intolerant so pay attention to how you feel when you eat cheese & adapt accordingly or opt for something like goat cheese that has less lactose than cheese from cow’s milk.⠀⠀⁠
.⠀⠀⁠
I personally like to mix in some quality cheese in moderation 😋⠀⠀⁠
.⠀⠀⁠
Some better cheese would be the ones below. They all have different nutrients and some beneficial compounds:⠀⠀⁠
.⠀⠀⁠
Mozzarella - contains bacteria that act as probiotics, including strains that may boost your immune system.⠀⠀⁠
.⠀⠀⁠
Cottage cheese - has much more protein than some other cheeses & also contains beneficial probiotics.⠀⠀⁠
.⠀⠀⁠
Blue cheese - boasts more calcium than most other cheeses. Blue cheese is cured with cultures from the mold Penicillium, which is what gives it a distinctive odor & tangy flavor. ⠀⠀⁠
.⠀⠀⁠
Goat cheese - a tangy, soft cheese made from goat’s milk which has more medium-chain fatty acids than cow’s milk. It also can be easier for some people to digest than other cheeses because goat’s milk is lower in lactose & has different proteins. ⠀⠀⁠
.⠀⠀⁠
Feta - typically made from sheep or goat’s milk. Feta provides conjugated linoleic acid (CLA), which has been associated with reduced body fat and improved body composition. ⠀⠀⁠
.⠀⠀⁠
Parmesan - made from raw, unpasteurized cow’s milk that’s aged for at least 12 months to kill harmful bacteria. Parmesan is full of calcium, phosphorus & lower in lactose.⁠
.⁠
#cheese

Healthy eating misconceptions! 🥗✨ *Swipe for two more*⁠⁠
⁠⁠
I wanted to clear up some of the misconceptions around switching to a more nutritious diet. While healthy eating looks different for everyone, I can safely say incorporating more whole foods in our diet will benefit almost anyone. Now, I do find when I’m encouraging people to upgrade their food, these misconceptions can block them from making the switch. Let’s breakdown each misconception below:⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Lie “You have to eat the same foods at almost every meal.” ▶️ Truth “You can eat a wide variety of healthy foods.” In fact, switching up your food on a daily or weekly basis can ensure you’re getting a variety of nutrients & minerals. Eating seasonally, trying new exotic fruits and veggies and switching up your protein sources are just some of the ways to keep your diet exciting!⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Lie “I have to cut out all complex carbs.” ▶️ Truth “Find the right amount of carbs for you and your activity level.” While a lot of people can benefit for going low carb for a period of time, going too low carb for too long can also be detrimental to your hormones and energy levels. As an active person, I find I feel my best when I make sure I’m getting at least one serving of fruit post workout and I’m incorporating some whole food carbs into meals like potatoes or rice.⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Lie “No fun foods allowed.” ▶️ “A healthy balance looks different for everyone.” I know I love incorporating planned treats into my healthy lifestyle! Now, how many treats you incorporate into your diet depends on your needs, wants and goals. I’m more of an 90% healthy foods, 10% fun foods kind of girl but many people flourish on more of an 80%/20% split so find what balance works for you!⁠⁠
⁠⁠
Hope you found this helpful. Let me know if you have any questions below.⠀⠀⠀⁠⁠

5 Delicious Ways to Enjoy Egg Cups! (Swipe to see what’s in each egg cup)⁠⁠
⁠⁠
If you’re a fan of egg cups then you’ll love these easy and tasty egg cup combinations. While there’s nothing wrong with enjoying some from your favorite coffee shop on occasion, making them yourself on a more regular basis can be a real game changer. This way you know exactly what’s in your food, plus you get to save the extras to enjoy later! A win-win :) ⁠
⁠⁠
Each of these combos makes 2-3 egg cups, so you can easily double the recipes if you’re meal prepping them. I like to season mine with salt, pepper, & garlic, but feel free to use what you prefer! Here are some egg cup combos  you can make at home in under 30 minutes. ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
What you need for the Broccoli & Cheddar:⁠⁠
-2-3 eggs⁠
-Handful of broccoli, chopped ⁠
-¼ cup shredded cheddar ⁠
-1 tbsp Avocado oil or olive oil ⁠⁠
-Seasoning⁠⁠
⁠⁠
What you need for the Prosciutto & Goat Cheese⁠
-2-3 eggs⁠
-2-3 pieces of prosciutto, chopped ⁠
-¼ cup goat cheese crumbles ⁠
-1 tbsp Avocado oil or olive oil ⁠⁠
-Seasoning of choice ⁠
⁠
What you need for the Tomato & Spinach:⁠⁠
-2-3 eggs ⁠
-Handful of grape tomatoes, halved ⁠
-½ cup spinach ⁠
-1 tbsp Avocado oil or olive oil ⁠⁠
-Seasoning ⁠
⁠
What you need for the Sausage & Mozzarella:⁠⁠
-2-3 eggs⁠
-½ cup sausage crumbles, cooked ⁠
-¼ cup shredded mozzarella ⁠
-1 tbsp Avocado oil or olive oil ⁠⁠
-Seasoning ⁠⁠
⁠⁠
What you need for the Bacon & Chive:⁠
-2-3 eggs⁠
-2-3 pieces bacon, cooked ⁠
-¼ cup chives, chopped ⁠
-1 tbsp Avocado oil or olive oil ⁠⁠
-Seasoning⁠
⁠⁠
What to do: ⁠⁠
1- Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F. ⁠⁠
2- Lightly coat a muffin tin with olive oil or avocado oil spray. ⁠
3- Beat the eggs and olive oil until fully combined.⁠
3- Pour the egg mixture ⅔ of the way into each muffin tray.⁠
4- Add in the ingredients of your choice (vegetables, cheese, etc) until the egg mixture almost reaches the top of the tin. ⁠
4- Bake for 15-20 minutes. Note: The egg cups will rise a good bit while baking. Once you remove them and let them cool, they will go down and can be removed from the muffin tray. ⁠
5- Enjoy right away or save for later! ⁠
⁠
#breakfast #healthyeating #paleo #mealprep
